This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video recognition tasks. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions reducing computational cost, which could indicate that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of multiplexer modules and the focus on efficiency could also suggest that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on improving recognition performance could indicate that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
